1. INTRODUCTION\par
   FastReport is reporting tool component. It consists of report engine,\par
designer and preview. It written on 100% Object Pascal and can be installed\par
in Delphi 4-7,2005 and C++Builder 4-6. Also available cross-platform version\par
FR CLX for Delphi 6,7 C++ Builder 6 and Kylix 1,2,3 - check out webpage to \par
get latest information. \par
\par
   FastReport 2.54 is "try before buy". See "Ordering" topic for details.\par
\par
\par
----------------------------------------------------------------------------\par
2. CAPABILITIES\par
- Fast, compact and flexible code allows you to extend FR functionality.\par
  No additional DLLs needed.\par
- Built-in powerful and easy-to-use designer (also available in run-time).\par
- Suitable MSWord-like report preview with "Search text" and "Edit" functions.\par
- Set of most useful components: Text, Line, Picture, Shape, OLE, RichText,\par
  Chart, Barcode. You can also write your own components.\par
- Ability to export your reports to other formats (such as TXT, RTF, CSV,\par
  HTML, PDF and other). \par
- Built-in Pascal-like language allows you write code without programming\par
  in Delphi. It allows you to create reports that can't be created in other\par
  tools.\par
- Script editor with syntax highligt.\par
- FR reports can contain dialogue forms that you can use to ask\par
  parameters before prepare a report. You can have as many dialogs as you need.\par
  FR uses the same designer for dialogs and have set of standart dialog\par
  controls like Button, Edit, CheckBox and other.\par
- Set of DB engines for FR allow you to create table/query/database components\par
  in run-time. Your reports can be completely independent of your application!\par
- FR can obtain data from tables and queries, arrays and data files - from\par
  any source. FR is not BDE-dependent, you can use it with *any* DB library\par
  that is based on standard TDataset component. You can also use FR with\par
  IB_Objects - powerful and wide-known library for Interbase DBMS.\par
- Localization in 21 languages. You can use FR in international applications.\par
- Full Bi-directional text output.\par
